text:
The coronavirus vaccine is here. Healthcare workers received the first Pfizer COVID-19 shots last week. 

But is it… https://t.co/2flx6VwdiB

name: businessinsider
text:
❓When can I get my vaccine? 

By late May, everyone in the US who wants a shot could have access. The CDC recommended that healthcare workers and nursing home residents be first in line. 

https://t.co/FAzfFvbhLC https://t.co/v4sAauhgqg

name: businessinsider
text:
❓ Do I still need to wear a mask? 

Absolutely. It will take many months for healthcare providers to give these shots to enough members of the public to make a dent in the pandemic. Plus, Pfizer’s and Moderna’s vaccines require two doses, weeks apart.
 
https://t.co/GvLzaqBiCI

name: businessinsider
text:
❓When can we have gatherings again? 

The end of 2021, and closer to 2022. Dr. Fauci told us it’s safer to wait until 2022 to host big weddings, birthdays and other celebrations. 

https://t.co/pUnZdPPaUY

name: businessinsider
text:
❓ How effective are the vaccines? 

Pfizer's vaccine was 95% effective at preventing symptomatic disease, while Moderna's vaccine was 94.1% effective at preventing symptomatic disease. We don't know if either vaccine can prevent asymptomatic spread. 

https://t.co/GvLzaqBiCI

name: businessinsider
text:
❓What are the side effects of the vaccine? 

You could get temporary side effects like fatigue, headache, and chills – which are completely normal following any immunization.

https://t.co/GvLzaqBiCI https://t.co/Y7WvFWWuZQ

name: businessinsider
text:
❓How diverse were the vaccine trials? 

Historically, vaccine trials have been pretty bad about leaving women and people of color out. However, the diversity in both trials mirrored the real world. 

Note: Pregnant women were not included in either trial. https://t.co/GvLzaqBiCI https://t.co/Hk2MRw7fHP

name: businessinsider
text:
❓How many vaccines are available? 

So far, at least 128,000 people have received doses of the Pfizer vaccine as of Dec. 18. You can check out this dashboard, hosted by @JohnsHopkins, to see how many vaccines have been administered in each state. 
https://t.co/yn1VPSsui0
